  "$comment": "Per-package gzipped fesm2022 bundle-size budget. The check script measures dist/packages/<pkg>/fesm2022/*.mjs and fails CI if any package exceeds its maxGz. Update with `node scripts/check-bundle-size.js --update` after an intentional growth and commit the diff in the same PR. Headroom is ~15% above the size at the time the entry was added (or +500B for tiny bundles), rounded to the nearest 100B — enough to absorb noise from re-exports / minor refactors but not enough to absorb a regression.",
  "headroomNote": "Tiny bundles (<2KB gz) get +500B; larger ones get ~15% rounded to nearest 100B.",
